                "name": "Theoretical",
                "url": "/topics/theoretical"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637851",
        "quote": "For those who have envisioned the State of Israel to be a democracy, which although primarily a Jewish polity for Jews is one in which non-Jews can become citizens and enjoy equal civil rights with the Jewish majority, the question of natural law is the question of human rights.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637851"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Enjoy",
                "url": "/topics/enjoy"
            },
            {
                "name": "Jewish",
                "url": "/topics/jewish"
            },
            {
                "name": "Primarily",
                "url": "/topics/primarily"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637852",
        "quote": "It has always been inevitable that, living as a small minority among a Christian majority, some Jews would convert to Christianity.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637852"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Small",
                "url": "/topics/small"
            },
            {
                "name": "Always",
                "url": "/topics/always"
            },
            {
                "name": "Inevitable",
                "url": "/topics/inevitable"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637853",
        "quote": "Unlike the issue of messiahhood, which arose when Jews and Christians were members of the same religio-political community and spoke the same conceptual language, the issues of the incarnation and the Trinity divide people who are no longer members of the same community and who no longer speak the same language.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637853"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Language",
                "url": "/topics/language"
            },
            {
                "name": "Issues",
                "url": "/topics/issues"
            },
            {
                "name": "Spoke",
                "url": "/topics/spoke"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637854",
        "quote": "Jewish status is defined by the divine election of Israel and his descendants. One does not become a Jew by one's own volition.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637854"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Election",
                "url": "/topics/election"
            },
            {
                "name": "Own",
                "url": "/topics/own"
            },
            {
                "name": "Jewish",
                "url": "/topics/jewish"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637856",
        "quote": "The religious doctrine of traditional Judaism entails the acceptance of the nationhood of the Jewish people and the everlasting sanctity of the Land of Israel for them.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637856"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Religious",
                "url": "/topics/religious"
            },
            {
                "name": "Entails",
                "url": "/topics/entails"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637858",
        "quote": "The work of man is to respond to the Covenant by obeying the commandments of the Torah, those commandments that can be obeyed here and now.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637858"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Here",
                "url": "/topics/here"
            },
            {
                "name": "Commandments",
                "url": "/topics/commandments"
            },
            {
                "name": "Covenant",
                "url": "/topics/covenant"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637859",
        "quote": "It was in the early 1960s that my late revered teacher, Professor Abraham Joshua Heschel, became the first major Jewish theologian in America to enter into dialogue with Christian theologians on a high theological level.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637859"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Revered",
                "url": "/topics/revered"
            },
            {
                "name": "Became",
                "url": "/topics/became"
            },
            {
                "name": "Theologians",
                "url": "/topics/theologians"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637860",
        "quote": "Theological reflection takes place within history, but the history within which it takes place is an ongoing, open-ended process.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637860"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Process",
                "url": "/topics/process"
            },
            {
                "name": "Which",
                "url": "/topics/which"
            },
            {
                "name": "Ongoing",
                "url": "/topics/ongoing"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637861",
        "quote": "The theological contacts between Jews and Christians during much of the premodern period are best characterized as disputations. Even when not engaged in face-to-face argumentation, Jews and Christians spoke about each other in essentially disputational terms.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637861"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            },
            {
                "name": "Engaged",
                "url": "/topics/engaged"
            },
            {
                "name": "Spoke",
                "url": "/topics/spoke"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637863",
        "quote": "Perhaps the main stumbling block to a better, and more fruitful, theological relationship with Judaism and the Jewish people has been the tendency of many Christian theologians to see the Christ event as the end of history.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637863"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Christ",
                "url": "/topics/christ"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            },
            {
                "name": "Theologians",
                "url": "/topics/theologians"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637864",
        "quote": "In a very real sense, Jews have to believe that Christians have missed the point about how to wait for the end, and Christians have to believe something quite similar about the Jews.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637864"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Wait",
                "url": "/topics/wait"
            },
            {
                "name": "Very",
                "url": "/topics/very"
            },
            {
                "name": "Similar",
                "url": "/topics/similar"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637816",
        "quote": "God chose us to live both in body and in soul, but the body functions for the sake of the soul more than the soul functions for the body.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637816"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Soul",
                "url": "/topics/soul"
            },
            {
                "name": "More",
                "url": "/topics/more"
            },
            {
                "name": "Functions",
                "url": "/topics/functions"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637818",
        "quote": "Historically, Jews only accept converts rather than actively seeking them.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637818"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Jews",
                "url": "/topics/jews"
            },
            {
                "name": "Than",
                "url": "/topics/than"
            },
            {
                "name": "Rather",
                "url": "/topics/rather"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637819",
        "quote": "If human language, with its logic, is the way God has given us to understand the world, then the Torah must be understood in that same language and with that same logic.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637819"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Torah",
                "url": "/topics/torah"
            },
            {
                "name": "Given",
                "url": "/topics/given"
            },
            {
                "name": "Human Language",
                "url": "/topics/human_language"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637820",
        "quote": "Cultural synthesis is how a compromise between various opinions is worked out. But truth does not change, and truth is not arrived at by some sort of compromise.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637820"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Change",
                "url": "/topics/change"
            },
            {
                "name": "Some",
                "url": "/topics/some"
            },
            {
                "name": "Synthesis",
                "url": "/topics/synthesis"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637821",
        "quote": "A fully positive relationship between Christians and Jews is one that would elide all differences.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637821"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Jews",
                "url": "/topics/jews"
            },
            {
                "name": "Christians",
                "url": "/topics/christians"
            },
            {
                "name": "Would",
                "url": "/topics/would"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637824",
        "quote": "Many of us, both Jews and Christians, want the public square to be pluralistic, which is neither partisan nor naked.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637824"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Jews",
                "url": "/topics/jews"
            },
            {
                "name": "Which",
                "url": "/topics/which"
            },
            {
                "name": "Christians",
                "url": "/topics/christians"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637825",
        "quote": "The shortcoming of purely political discourse between Christians and Jews arises from the fact that it is largely built upon the perception of a common enemy.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637825"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Common Enemy",
                "url": "/topics/common_enemy"
            },
            {
                "name": "Fact",
                "url": "/topics/fact"
            },
            {
                "name": "Purely",
                "url": "/topics/purely"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637826",
        "quote": "All modern secularity requires is that our public norms and the arguments for them not presuppose common acceptance of Jewish or Christian revelation, even if these public norms are consistent with a particular community's revelation and the authoritative teachings it derives from that revelation.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637826"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Jewish",
                "url": "/topics/jewish"
            },
            {
                "name": "Our",
                "url": "/topics/our"
            },
            {
                "name": "Revelation",
                "url": "/topics/revelation"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637827",
        "quote": "To be a Jew, essentially and not just accidentally, is to regard the Jewish people as one's sole primal community. Election by the unique God requires total and unconditional loyalty to one people.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637827"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Election",
                "url": "/topics/election"
            },
            {
                "name": "Primal",
                "url": "/topics/primal"
            },
            {
                "name": "Sole",
                "url": "/topics/sole"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637828",
        "quote": "There is no question that Israelis - indeed, all concerned Jews - have to continue to work out a Jewish public philosophy that truly justifies a Jewish state in the land of Israel.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637828"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "No Question",
                "url": "/topics/no_question"
            },
            {
                "name": "Jewish State",
                "url": "/topics/jewish_state"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637829",
        "quote": "Jews have not only become equal citizens in Western democracies, they have become leading citizens. And, of course, the reestablishment of the State of Israel has given Jews a political presence in the world they have not had since biblical times.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637829"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Leading",
                "url": "/topics/leading"
            },
            {
                "name": "Jews",
                "url": "/topics/jews"
            },
            {
                "name": "Given",
                "url": "/topics/given"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637830",
        "quote": "Christians and Jews alike are the new exiles of the contemporary world, struggling with how to sing the Lord's song in a strange land.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637830"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Song",
                "url": "/topics/song"
            },
            {
                "name": "New",
                "url": "/topics/new"
            },
            {
                "name": "Christians",
                "url": "/topics/christians"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637833",
        "quote": "In deciding among theological views, one should be something of a consequentialist: the choice of one theological position over another should be, if not actually determined, at least heavily conditioned by the fact that it implies a better ethical outcome than the alternatives.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637833"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Fact",
                "url": "/topics/fact"
            },
            {
                "name": "Another",
                "url": "/topics/another"
            },
            {
                "name": "Least",
                "url": "/topics/least"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637834",
        "quote": "All the questions discussed in the Talmud and related rabbinic literature are normative questions: either they are questions of what one is to think or what one is to do. Every prescribed thought has some practical implication; every prescribed act has some theoretical implication.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637834"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Think",
                "url": "/topics/think"
            },
            {
                "name": "Some",
                "url": "/topics/some"
            },
            {
                "name": "Practical",
                "url": "/topics/practical"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637835",
        "quote": "At the political level, most Jews and most Catholics have accepted the liberal idea of religious freedom.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637835"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Freedom",
                "url": "/topics/freedom"
            },
            {
                "name": "Most",
                "url": "/topics/most"
            },
            {
                "name": "Religious",
                "url": "/topics/religious"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637836",
        "quote": "One cannot accept Christ and still be part of the normative Jewish community; one cannot live by Torah and still be part of the Church.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637836"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Christ",
                "url": "/topics/christ"
