            {
                "name": "Parent",
                "url": "/topics/parent"
            },
            {
                "name": "Deceased",
                "url": "/topics/deceased"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637840",
        "quote": "I first came to Jewish-Catholic relations in 1963, while studying for the rabbinate at the Jewish Theological Seminary in New York.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637840"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Studying",
                "url": "/topics/studying"
            },
            {
                "name": "New",
                "url": "/topics/new"
            },
            {
                "name": "Jewish",
                "url": "/topics/jewish"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637841",
        "quote": "Each person is responsible only for his or her own sins. Even the Christian doctrine of 'original sin' does not mean that humans are punished for the sin of the first human pair but, rather, that humans seem inevitably to copy the sin of the first human pair.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637841"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Own",
                "url": "/topics/own"
            },
            {
                "name": "Seem",
                "url": "/topics/seem"
            },
            {
                "name": "Rather",
                "url": "/topics/rather"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637842",
        "quote": "The Jewish tradition presents itself as the greatest revelation of God's truth that can be known in the world. That is why we call ourselves 'the chosen people.' It is not that we choose ourselves. It means that we have been elected by God and given the Torah.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637842"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            },
            {
                "name": "Means",
                "url": "/topics/means"
            },
            {
                "name": "Given",
                "url": "/topics/given"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637844",
        "quote": "The right to privacy has both positive and negative connotations for those who consider themselves part of the natural law tradition.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637844"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Law",
                "url": "/topics/law"
            },
            {
                "name": "Natural",
                "url": "/topics/natural"
            },
            {
                "name": "Part",
                "url": "/topics/part"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637845",
        "quote": "Every individual is a person necessarily imbedded in a range of multiple relations, and therefore, no one is really independent in anything but a relative sense; no one is truly autonomous.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637845"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Independent",
                "url": "/topics/independent"
            },
            {
                "name": "Individual",
                "url": "/topics/individual"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637846",
        "quote": "To view any individual as being independent of relationality is like viewing a point outside of a line, a line outside of a figure, a figure outside of a body.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637846"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Individual",
                "url": "/topics/individual"
            },
            {
                "name": "Like",
                "url": "/topics/like"
            },
            {
                "name": "Figure",
                "url": "/topics/figure"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637847",
        "quote": "Foundational autonomy asserts instead that in the most fundamental practical sense, I am my own creator, which means that at the core, I am alone.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637847"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Creator",
                "url": "/topics/creator"
            },
            {
                "name": "Which",
                "url": "/topics/which"
            },
            {
                "name": "Means",
                "url": "/topics/means"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637848",
        "quote": "Modernity has been largely shaped for Jews by three momentous experiences: the acquisition of citizenship by individual Jews in secular nation-states, the destruction of one-third of Jewry in the Holocaust, and the founding of the State of Israel.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637848"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Individual",
                "url": "/topics/individual"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            },
            {
                "name": "One-Third",
                "url": "/topics/one-third"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637849",
        "quote": "During the Middle Ages, Jews were members of a semi-independent polity within a larger polity.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David Novak",
            "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637849"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Within",
                "url": "/topics/within"
            },
            {
                "name": "Middle",
                "url": "/topics/middle"
            },
            {
                "name": "Larger",
                "url": "/topics/larger"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_novak_637817",
        "quote": "The Holocaust, taken by itself, is a black hole. To look at it directly is to be swallowed up by it.",
